      "### Page 1",
      "Cloud Deployment and Service ModelsServicios y Aplicaciones Distribuidas",
      "![Page 1, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_001.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 2",
      "Cloud Computing Recap",
      "â€¢Shared pool of compute, storage, networking on demand.â€¢On-demand self-service, broad access, elasticity.â€¢Measured service: pay for what you use.",
      "![Page 2, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_002.png)",
      "![Page 2, Figure 2](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_002_img_001.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 3",
      "Why Service Models Matter",
      "â€¢They define the abstraction level you consume.â€¢Control vs convenience trade-off changes per model.â€¢Impacts agility, cost, and who is responsible for what.",
      "![Page 3, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_003.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 4",
      "IaaS: Definition & Scope",
      "â€¢Virtualized compute, storage, networking primitives.â€¢You manage OS, runtime, middleware, data, apps.â€¢Examples: EC2, Azure VMs, Google Compute Engine.",
      "![Page 4, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_004.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 5",
      "IaaS: Benefits and Challenges",
      "â€¢Benefits: flexibility, compatibility, fine-grained control.â€¢Challenges: patching, capacity planning, more ops toil.â€¢Mitigation: golden images, IaC, autoscaling groups.",
      "![Page 5, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_005.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 6",
      "PaaS: Definition & Scope",
      "â€¢Deploy code; platform manages runtime, scaling, and OS.â€¢Opinionated buildpacks and service bindings.â€¢Examples: Heroku, Azure App Service, AWS Elastic Beanstalk.",
      "![Page 6, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_006.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 7",
      "PaaS: Benefits and Challenges",
      "â€¢Benefits: faster delivery, less undifferentiated heavy lifting.â€¢Challenges: platform constraints, vendor features vary.â€¢Mitigation: 12-factor practices, clear SLOs, platform guardrails.",
      "![Page 7, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_007.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 8",
      "SaaS: Definition & Scope",
      "â€¢Complete application delivered as a service.â€¢Provider manages everything; you configure and consume.â€¢Examples: Gmail, Salesforce, GitHub, Slack.",
      "![Page 8, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_008.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 9",
      "SaaS: Benefits and Challenges",
      "â€¢Benefits: fastest time to value, minimal ops burden.â€¢Challenges: customization limits, data/control constraints.â€¢Mitigation: evaluate APIs, export paths, compliance posture.",
      "![Page 9, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_009.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 10",
      "IaaS vs PaaS vs SaaS (Responsibilities)â€¢IaaS: you manage OS â†’ app; provider manages hardware.â€¢PaaS: you manage code & data; provider manages runtime & OS.â€¢SaaS: you manage config & users; provider runs the app.",
      "![Page 10, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_010.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 11",
      "Choosing the Right Model",
      "â€¢Drivers: time-to-market, control needs, compliance, skills.â€¢Workload traits: variability, latency needs, statefulness.â€¢Evolve per serviceâ€”mixed models across a portfolio.",
      "![Page 11, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_011.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 12",
      "Cloud Providers Overview",
      "â€¢Major hyperscalers: AWS, Azure, Google Cloud.â€¢All offer IaaS/PaaS/SaaS building blocks.â€¢Differ in strengths, ecosystem, and pricing models.",
      "![Page 12, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_012.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 13",
      "AWS: Strengths & Focus Areas",
      "â€¢Breadth/depth of services; rich ecosystem.â€¢Mature IaaS (EC2, VPC), serverless (Lambda), data (S3).â€¢Marketplace, partners, and global footprint.",
      "![Page 13, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_013.png)",
