      "â€¢Enterprise integration with Microsoft stack.â€¢Hybrid tooling (Azure Arc), strong identity (Entra ID/AAD).â€¢Windows/.NET first-class, growing Linux/K8s support.",
      "![Page 14, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_014.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 15",
      "Google Cloud: Strengths & Focus Areas",
      "â€¢Data, analytics, and ML leadership (BigQuery, Vertex AI).â€¢Innovations in containers and SRE practices.â€¢High-performance networking.",
      "![Page 15, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_015.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 16",
      "Multi-Cloud and Portability",
      "â€¢Reasons: resilience, data locality, negotiation leverage.â€¢Costs: duplicated ops, lowest-common-denominator designs.â€¢Pragmatic approach: portable apps; non-portable data/analytics.",
      "![Page 16, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_016.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 17",
      "Public Cloud: Definition & Benefits",
      "â€¢Shared infrastructure operated by a provider.â€¢Elasticity, global reach, rapid innovation.â€¢Lower upfront capex; pay-as-you-go.",
      "![Page 17, Figure 1](subjects/Sad/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes-images/Session_3_Cloud_Service_Models_Bullets_Notes_page_017.png)",
