      "### Page 19",
      "Other features",
      "â€¢ Zero Crossing Rate",
      "â€¢ the rate at which the signal changes from positive to negative or back.",
      "â€¢ Harmonics and Percusive decomposition",
      "â€¢ Harmonics are characteristics that represents the sound color",
      "â€¢ Percusive components represents the sound rhythm and emotion",
      "â€¢ Tempo BMP (beats per minute)",
      "â€¢ Dynamic programming beat tracker.",
      "â€¢ Spectral Centroid",
      "â€¢ indicates where the â€centre of massâ€ of the spectrum of a sound is located and is calculated as the",
      "weighted mean of the frequencies present in the sound.",
      "â€¢ Spectral Contrast",
      "â€¢ measures the difference in amplitude between peaks and valleys in the audio spectrum",
      "â€¢ Spectral Rolloff",
      "â€¢ is a measure of the shape of the signal spectrum. It represents the frequency below which a specified",
      "percentage of the total spectral energy, e.g. 85%, lies",
      "â€¢ Chroma Frequencies",
      "â€¢ Interesting and powerful representation for music audio in which the entire spectrum is projected onto 12",
