      "1. RNN Basics",
      "â€¢ Process sequential data by maintaining hidden state   ht = f(Wx * xt + Wh * ht-1 + b)",
      "â€¢ Each timestep considers current input and previous state",
      "â€¢ Share parameters across time steps",
      "â€¢ Natural fit for variable-length speech sequences",
      "3. Limitations with Long Sequences",
      "a) Vanishing Gradients",
      "â€¢ Gradients become extremely small during backpropagation",
      "â€¢ Early inputs lose influence over time",
      "â€¢ Makes learning long-term dependencies difficult",
      "â€¢ Critical issue for long speech utterances",
      "â€¢ b) Exploding Gradients",
      "â€¢ Gradients become extremely large",
      "â€¢ Leads to unstable training",
      "â€¢ Can cause numerical overflow",
      "â€¢ Requires gradient clipping",
      "4. Practical Impact on Speech Processing",
      "â€¢ Poor performance on long utterances",
      "â€¢ Difficulty capturing long-range dependencies",
      "â€¢ Limited context window in practice",
      "â€¢ Memory inefficiency for long sequences",
      "![Page 11, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 6 SPEECH-images/Chapter 6 SPEECH_page_011.png)",
