      "### Page 20",
      "End-to-End ASR Systems vs Traditional Pipeline",
      "1.Traditional Pipeline",
      "â€¢ Separate components: acoustic model, pronunciation model, language model",
      "â€¢ Each component trained independently",
      "â€¢ Complex integration and optimization",
      "â€¢ Requires expert knowledge for each component",
      "â€¢ Error propagation between stages",
      "2.End-to-End Approach",
      "â€¢ Single neural network",
      "â€¢ Direct audio-to-text conversion",
      "â€¢ Joint optimization of all components",
      "â€¢ Trained on <audio, transcript> pairs",
      "â€¢ Simpler training and deployment",
      "![Page 20, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 6 SPEECH-images/Chapter 6 SPEECH_page_020.png)",
