      "### Page 64",
      "GloVe",
      "â€¢ Global Vectors for word representation is another famous embedding",
      "technique used quite often in NLP .",
      "â€¢ Proposed in  2014 by Jeffery Pennington, Richard Socher & Christopher D",
      "Manning from Stanford.",
      "â€¢ It tries to overcome the 2nd disadvantage of word2vec mentioned before",
      "by trying to learn both local & global statistics of a word to represent it.",
      "â€¢ It tries to encompass the best of:",
      "â€¢ count-based technique (co-occurrence matrix) &",
      "â€¢ prediction-based technique (Word2Vec)",
      "â€¢ â€¦ and hence is also referred to as a hybrid technique for continuous word",
      "representation",
      "![Page 64, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_064.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 65",
      "GloVe - Mathematical Foundation",
      "â€¢ It is designed to generate word embeddings by capturing global statistical",
      "information from a corpus. The key idea is to factorize the co-occurrence matrix",
      "to learn word vectors.",
      "Key Concepts",
      "1.Co-occurrence Matrix:",
      "1. This matrix X is constructed from a corpus where each entry Xij represents the number of",
      "times word j appears in the context of word i",
      "2. For example, if \"cat\" and \"pet\" often appear together, Xcat,pet pet will be high.",
      "2.Objective:",
      "1. Capture the ratio of co-occurrence probabilities between words to reflect semantic",
      "relationships.",
      "![Page 65, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_065.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 66",
      "GloVe - Co-occurrence Matrix",
      "â€¢ The co-occurrence matrix is a core component of the GloVe model. It records",
      "how often pairs of words appear together within a specified context window.",
      "â€¢ Each cell (i, j) in the matrix represents the number of times Word i appears in the",
      "context of Word j within a given window size.",
      "Word1 Word2 Word3 Word4",
      "Word1 0 2 3 0",
      "Word2 2 0 1 4",
      "Word3 3 1 0 5",
      "Word4 0 4 5 0",
      "![Page 66, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_066.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 67",
      "The GloVe",
      "Loss",
