      "### Page 68",
      "Training GloVe",
      "â€¢ Co-occurrence Matrix: Construct a matrix capturing how often words",
      "appear together in a corpus.",
      "â€¢ Objective: Learn word vectors by minimizing the difference between",
      "their dot products and the logarithm of their co-occurrence counts.",
      "â€¢ Weighting Function: Balances the influence of word pairs, giving",
      "appropriate importance to frequent and infrequent pairs.",
      "â€¢ Optimization: Use an algorithm like stochastic gradient descent to",
      "adjust word vectors until the model converges.",
      "â€¢ Result: Word embeddings that effectively capture word meanings and",
      "relationships",
      "![Page 68, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_068.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 69",
      "Hyperparameters in GloVe",
      "â€¢ Vector Dimension (d):",
      "â€¢ Determines the size of the word embeddings.",
      "â€¢ Higher dimensions capture more semantic nuances but require more computation.",
      "â€¢ Context Window Size:",
      "â€¢ Defines the range of words considered for co-occurrence.",
      "â€¢ Larger windows capture broader context but may introduce noise.",
      "â€¢ Learning Rate:",
      "â€¢ Controls the step size during optimization.",
      "â€¢ Needs careful tuning to ensure convergence without overshooting.",
      "â€¢ Number of Iterations:",
      "â€¢ Specifies how many times the model processes the data.",
      "â€¢ More iterations can improve accuracy but increase training time.",
      "â€¢ Weighting Function Parameters:",
      "â€¢ Adjusts how co-occurrence frequencies influence training.",
      "â€¢ Balances the contribution of frequent and rare pairs.",
      "![Page 69, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_069.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 70",
      "Advantages of GloVe over Word2Vec",
      "â€¢ Global context: Uses the entire corpus, capturing broader semantic",
      "relationships.",
      "â€¢ Efficiency: Can be trained faster than Word2Vec for large datasets.",
      "â€¢ because it uses a precomputed co-occurrence matrix, leveraging the entire",
      "corpus efficiently",
      "â€¢ GloVe's optimization involves just solving a matrix factorization problem",
      "â€¢ this reduces data processing and simplifies optimization compared to",
      "Word2Vec's iterative neural network approach",
      "â€¢ Improved performance: Often shows better performance on word",
      "analogy tasks.",
      "![Page 70, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_070.png)",
      "",
      "### Page 71",
      "GloVe â€“ Advantages & Disadvantages",
      "Advantages",
      "â€¢ It tends to perform better than word2vec in analogy tasks",
      "â€¢ It considers word pair to word pair relationship while constructing the vectors &",
      "hence tend to add more meaning to the vectors when compared to vectors",
      "constructed from word-word relationships",
      "â€¢ GloVe is easier to parallelise compared to Word2Vec hence shorter training time",
      "Disadvantages",
      "â€¢ Because it uses a co-occurrence matrix & global information, memory cost is",
      "more in GloVe compared to word2vec",
      "â€¢ Similar to word2vec, it does not solve the problem of polysemous words since",
      "words & vectors have a one-to-one relationship",
      "![Page 71, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_071.png)",
      "",
