      "### Page 80",
      "FastTextvs Word2Vec",
      "â€¢ Word2Vec treats each word as a single unit",
      "â€¢ FastText breaks words into subword units (n-grams), allowing it to:",
      "â€¢ Handle out-of-vocabulary words",
      "â€¢ Better understand morphologically rich languagesLearn representations for rare words",
      "â€¢ Word2Vec learns representations for complete words only",
      "â€¢ FastText learns representations for both words and subwords (character n-grams)",
      "â€¢ Word2Vec: Faster training, smaller memory footprint",
      "â€¢ FastText: Slower training, larger memory requirements due to subword storage",
      "â€¢ Word2Vec: Better for languages with simple morphology (like English)",
      "â€¢ FastText: Better for languages with complex morphology (Finnish, Turkish, German)",
      "![Page 80, Figure 1](subjects/snlp/slides/Chapter 4 NLP-images/Chapter 4 NLP_page_080.png)",
